# ARIA Agent — Cursor Rules
# Read this file first, every session, before doing anything.

## What is ARIA
Autonomous Rope Intelligence Architecture — wall-mounted lead climbing auto-belay
device targeting the US market gap in lead climbing automation. Open source.
Provisional patent filed. Built by Jonathan Kofman (Northeastern MEng + Georgia Tech OMSCS).

## Repo Map
- Root Python files     → dashboard tabs, CEM simulation, state machine, cert tooling
- aria_models/          → physics models: dynamic drop, static tests, state machine
- cad/fusion_scripts/   → Fusion 360 Python API scripts for all mechanical parts
- firmware/stm32/       → Safety layer (STM32F411 Black Pill) — C++
- firmware/esp32/       → Intelligence layer (XIAO ESP32-S3 Sense) — Arduino
- tools/                → Utilities: simulator, PID tuner, audio collection, HIL test
- docs/                 → System specs, setup guides, safety monitoring, app spec
- dataset/              → Edge Impulse voice command audio (8 classes)
- aria-climb/           → React Native / Expo companion app
- context/              → [KNOWLEDGE BASE] Read these before any engineering task
- sessions/             → Agent session logs go here

## Current Build Phase
Phase 2-3: Motor + PID software + voice command integration.
Hardware not yet arrived. Build and validate software first.

## Agent Behavior Rules
1. READ context/ folder before writing any code
2. READ context/aria_failures.md before any Fusion script work
3. PLAN operation sequence in plain language BEFORE generating code
4. On failure: diagnose, update context/aria_failures.md, retry — do NOT ask user
5. Never hardcode geometry — all constants live in context/aria_mechanical.md
6. Never bypass STM32 safety layer logic under any circumstance
7. After each session: write a brief log to sessions/YYYY-MM-DD_task.md
8. If retried 3x without success: write diagnosis to sessions/ and stop with summary

## Hardware Architecture
- STM32F411 Black Pill  → safety layer: watchdog, fault detection, clutch control
- XIAO ESP32-S3 Sense   → intelligence: voice (Edge Impulse), BLE, CV, state logic
- BLDC motor            → slack management via 30:1 planetary gearbox
- Centrifugal clutch    → 200mm brake drum, primary fall arrest (Lead Solo design)
- Rope spool            → 600mm, 6061 aluminum housing, wall-mounted behind panel

## System States
IDLE → CLIMBING → CLIPPING → TAKE → REST → LOWER → WATCH_ME → UP

## Critical Constraints
- STM32 safety layer is NEVER bypassed — all state transitions validated there
- Fusion scripts MUST use Direct Design mode (not Parametric)
- Fusion geometry: solid box first → cut interior → features on existing faces
- Never use annular profile extrusion (known failure mode)
- All constants from context/aria_mechanical.md, never inline magic numbers

