## CEM Integration
- Every generated part runs CEM checks appropriate to its type
- Static SF < 1.5 = hard failure in future revisions; currently surfaced as a strong warning
- Static SF 1.5–2.0 = warning, outputs saved with flag
- Static SF >= 2.0 = pass
- See context/aria_materials.md for yield strengths
- See context/aria_test_standards.md for ANSI limits
- Meta JSON at outputs/cad/meta/<part>.json contains extracted dims (bbox; part-specific dims can be added by generators)

## ARIA-OS Command Reference

### Generation
  python run_aria_os.py "describe part"
  -> planner -> CadQuery generation -> geometry validation -> CEM check -> STEP/STL
  Output: outputs/cad/step/, outputs/cad/stl/, outputs/cad/generated_code/, outputs/cad/meta/

### Modification  
  python run_aria_os.py --modify "outputs/cad/generated_code/<part>.py" "what to change"
  -> loads existing code -> LLM modifies specific feature only -> validates -> exports as _mod1, _mod2...

### Assembly
  python run_aria_os.py --assemble assembly_configs/<config>.json
  -> imports multiple STEPs -> positions them -> exports single assembly STEP/STL

### Inspection
  python run_aria_os.py --list        -> all parts with sizes and validation status
  python run_aria_os.py --validate    -> re-validate all STEPs, exit 1 if any fail

### Optimization (new)
  python run_aria_os.py --optimize "outputs/cad/generated_code/<part>.py" --goal "minimize_weight" --constraint "SF>=2.0" --constraint "wall>=6mm"
  -> parametric sweep -> score each variant -> return best design

### Optimizer + Auto-Regenerate
  python run_aria_os.py --optimize-and-regenerate <part_stub> --goal <goal> --constraint <rule> [--material <material_id>]
  -> optimize -> (optional) material recommendation -> auto-generate part at optimal dimensions -> validate -> export STEP/STL

### CEM Full System Check (new)
  python run_aria_os.py --cem-full
  -> runs CEM checks across ALL generated parts -> system-level report

### Generate and Assemble (new)
  python run_aria_os.py --generate-and-assemble "part description" --into assembly_configs/<config>.json --as "part_label" --at "x,y,z"
  -> generates part -> validates -> adds to assembly config -> re-runs assembly

## Firmware Sync

### ESP32 Sync
  python tools/aria_constants_sync.py --from-cem --esp32
  -> checks STM32 + ESP32 shared constants for drift
  -> with --patch: updates ESP32 thresholds to match STM32 values
     (comms constants like UART_BAUD are checked, never patched)

## Dashboard
  python -m streamlit run aria_dashboard.py
  -> includes "ARIA-OS (CAD & manufacturing)" with a "CAD & Manufacturing" view

## Template Override Detection
  [TEMPLATE] = validated template used (no LLM call, fastest)
  [LLM] Overrides detected -> LLM used, explicit dims respected
  [LLM] Unknown part -> LLM used

## CEM Routing by Part Type
  pawl/lever/ratchet/shaft/collar/spool -> static SF check only
  housing -> static + dynamic drop + full CEM system check
  motor/mount/plate/guide -> no CEM check

## Output Structure
  outputs/cad/step/          -> STEP files (gitignored, regenerable)
  outputs/cad/stl/           -> STL files (gitignored, regenerable)
  outputs/cad/generated_code/-> raw LLM Python (gitignored)
  outputs/cad/meta/          -> dimension JSON (tracked in git)
  assembly_configs/          -> assembly JSON configs (tracked in git)
  sessions/                  -> agent session logs (tracked in git)

